IBADAN – Senator Bola Ahmed Tinubu, the National Leader of All Progressive Congress APC has promised his unflinching support for the family of late Olubadan of Ibadanland, Oba Saliu Adetunji Ajeoguguniso 1. Tinubu made the declaration on Saturday during his visit to the Palace of the late monarch at Popoyema area of Ibadan. Tinubu who arrived the palace about few minutes after five was accompanied by Chief Bayo Adelabu, the Oyo State APC gubernatorial aspirant at the 2019 general elections, James Faleke Otunba Rotimi Ajanaku, Senator Rilwan Adesoji Akanbi and others stressed that he was at the Palace to greet the Olori and the entire family of the late Oba Adetunji over the demise of their father who he described as a great monarch during his lifetime and father of all. I Endorsed Tinubu For Presidency In 2019, I Have Rejected Him… (UPDATED) 2023: APC Does Not Belong To Tinubu, Says Kalu He said, “I’m here to greet the Olori, the entire family over the demise of our Baba who has gone to join his ancestors, when Baba came to Burdillon, I don’t know he came to bid me farewell, he prayed for me on that day. “Baba was a very great man, very industrious and hard working, very loyal,very honest, God Almighty is the one that knows when anyone of us will leave this world, during his reign everything was peaceful. “Olori I can assure you and the children that as long as I continue to live you will know no suffering, I’m promising you all my support. Tinubu said. Tinubu had earlier visited the palace of Soun of Ogbomoso to condole with the family over the demise of Oba Jimoh Oyewumi Ajagungnade III, he also paid a condolence visit to Agodi Government Secretariat Ibadan where he was as received by the state Governor Engr Seyi Makinde and the state top officials.